Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim
and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Trim and
thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn
off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Rinse and wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking
water, then drain.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for
mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until just
softened, ~{30 seconds to 1%minute}. Add @flour{1%tablespoon} and cook,
stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}. Whisk in @milk{6.75%ounce} and
⅓ cup pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4), making sure to eliminate any flour
clumps. Let simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} into pan with sauce until melted. Stir in
mushrooms, gemelli, and @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt and
pepper.

> If needed, stir in reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is
> coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and
scallion greens. Serve.